title: Desktop Holder for Mini Heavy Duty Filament Spool

description.text: Modification of the PFP spool stand to hold my mini heavy duty filament spool. I had to clip the ends off the arms to make it work but it keeps the spool off the table. You may need a clamp or something (perhaps /thing:12616 ) to hold it down, tho.
Print the 2 parts and screw them together with a standard wood screw. Print a Mini Heavy Duty Filament Spool and put it on.

description.text: This thing was made with Tinkercad. Edit it online https://tinkercad.com/things/hema8iOjffV

This is a first example of this library which shows how easy it is to use it for Meccano(R) projects. The code for this object was 5 lines in OpenSCAD! This is due to reuse of libraries. I hope this encourages people to use such libraries and perhaps create Lego to Meccano interfaces and such! See the robot-tilt-webcam.scad file for the implementation. See the part this is derived from to find my original Meccano Lib. See ballJoint.scad for a ballJoint script. It is currently only used for the ball, but the joint can be used equally easily.

title: Door Linkage Plastic Piece for F-150

description.text:
Plastic piece from my 97 F-150 door linkage, its the go-between for the rod that unlatches the door and the handle mechanism.
The original piece is a bit more intricate and I'm not sure if i want to replicate the whole thing or just enough to get the door working again :D
But ill keep the Sketchup file updated at least.
And of course, if you can make it better, by all means make a derivative :D (I'm better in Sketchup than in OpenSCAD so this is what most of my Things will be)
Uploaded the OpenSCAD file for it. This one attempts to use a pin of some sort to keep it in the latch hole.

Download the sketchup or STL and print.
At the moment my printer cant do overhangs that well, but it being a little messy shouldn't hurt the functionality of the part

A Cup for whater or something else.
  • Cup.stl -> the whole Cup for one extruder
  • CupOnly.stl -> only the cup to complete with the next one:
  • Ground.stl -> the 'Ground' for the cup, if you want to use two extruder
    • TWO EXTRUDER SUPPORT!
    (easily with Cura 14.03) Copy 'CupOnly.stl' and 'Ground.stl' into Cura (with two extruder enabled) and klick right klick. Then take 'Dual extrusion merge' while you right klick on one of the both objekts.
    If you want you can scale it.
